<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="11" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="12.[192,1440,483,571]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,335,483,507]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Lack of distinct brush on metatibia (especially in males); inferior lobes of eyes in males less contiguous; abdomen densely pubescent (in males long and erect, in female shorter and less erect). 
<collectingRegion box="[192,267,547,571]" country="Argentina" name="Chaco" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Chaco</collectingRegion>
forest species.
</paragraph>
